But I wanted my project to be able to track the time based on where the sun was so then I coded it to be able to determine the time based on where the sun is so Tracking time based on the sun’s position in your code was done by calculating the Local Solar Time using astronomical algorithms, rather than relying on a standard clock. The core concept is that the Sun reaches its highest point (solar noon) when it crosses the observer's local meridian, moving across the sky at approximately \(15^{\circ }\) per hour (\(360^{\circ }\) rotation in 24 hours). 
